cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a novel dataset for evaluating 6-DOF object tracking algorithms and conducts an extensive study of a deep 6-DOF tracking architecture. It is also likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it evaluates the robustness of the trackers to occlusion and challenging interactions between a person and the object. The paper also discusses the training methodology and the optimization of parameters, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a pipeline for acquiring accurate ground truth poses of real objects, which could make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
